# [[patterned]] [[window]]; a [[clear]] and [[bright]] window; [[shining]], [[brightness]]
#:{{Hani|《說文‧囧部》：“'''囧'''，窗牖麗廔闓明，象形。”}}
#::''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'': "'''''Jiong''' — An open and light window. Pictographic.''"
#:{{Hani|《文選‧江淹〈雜體詩‧效張綽“雜述”〉》：“'''囧囧'''秋月明，憑軒詠堯老。”}}
#::Jiang Yan, "Miscellaneous Poems — ''Imitation of Zhang Chuo's 'Miscellaneous Writing'''", from the anthology of ''{{w|Wen Xuan}}'': "''The moonlight at an autumn night was '''brightly clean'''; I leaned on the railing, chanting poems and savouring the logics of the ancient sages (lit. of {{w|Emperor Yao|Yao}} and {{w|Laozi}}).''"
# {{neologism|slang|jocular|lang=cmn}} an [[emoticon]] expressing [[surprise]], [[shock]], [[embarrassment]], [[helplessness]] or [[awkwardness]]
#:{{Hani|新華網《[http://big5.xinhuanet.com/gate/big5/news.xinhuanet.com/overseas/2011-06/07/c_121501794.htm 眾名人爆料高考囧事]》：“而那些生活在光環中的明星和名人們，曾經也有過類似的經歷，他們難忘的往事中也不乏趣聞和'''囧'''事…… 李想在高三時選擇放棄高考，卻成功創業，身價上億。”}}
#::''Xinhua'', "Celebrities reveal their embarrassing moments before/at the {{w|National Higher Education Entrance Examination|University Entrance Examination}}": "''The celebrities and notabilities now living under spotlights used to have similar experiences; there was no lack of amusing anecdotes and '''embarrassing''' moments in their unforgettable pasts ... Li Xiang dropped out of school during the third year of high school, choosing not to take the University Entrance Examination. Instead, he successfully started an enterprise, now worth hundreds of millions.''"

====Usage notes====
An [[emoticon]] used to express [[helplessness]] or [[awkwardness]], usually in a humourous way. This usage gained popularity on Taiwanese [[forums]] (aka "[[BBS]]"), then spread through the media to Hong Kong, and eventually to Mainland China. Its meaning was influenced by the homophonic character (in Beijing Mandarin) {{Hani|[[窘]]}} ("hard-pressed; embarrassed").

